# Netlify redirects

# Template routing. /contact now resolves to its own shell (Phase 9).
# Every other unmatched path is treated as a project slug and serves
# project.html; its main.js inspects the slug and either renders the
# project or silently redirects to / when the slug is unknown.
/contact   /contact.html   200
/*         /project.html   200

# Legacy hash URLs (/#morro etc., listed in BUILD_SPEC.md §4) are NOT
# redirected. Browsers don't send the fragment to the server, so Netlify
# never sees the #morro part — every /#x request arrives here as /, and
# we serve the home page as-is. Shared legacy links land on /; the slug
# migration map in the spec is retained for historical reference only.
